Tourism SA JOHANNESBURG - Three board members from the South African Tourism board have resigned. Enver Duminy, Ravi Nadasen and Rosemary Anderson have resigned with immediate effect. READ: Tourism Department responds to Tottenham Hotspur deal Their resignations have been received by tourism minister Lindiwe Sisulu. Their departures come as questions and scrutiny around the R900-million Tottenham Hotspurs deal continue.